FBIS3-54242 "drnes016_l_94017" FBIS-NES-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Shahal: All Crude Oil Now Bought in Arab World TA2401202994 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew 1800 GMT 24 Jan 94 TA2401202994 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Israel is currently purchasing all its crude oil in the Arab world, 40 percent from Egypt, and the rest from other Arab states via intermediaries. Energy Minister Moshe Shahal today officially announced that Israel has stopped buying oil in Mexico.
